{"key":"processedPost-20414554","value":{"id":20414554,"first":20413929,"last":20418547,"when":1407977432,"utime":"08/14/14 03:50 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>Kalypto said:</b><br />Im not talking about inoculating bulk substrate with agar I never said anything about substrate <br /><br />Im asking why RR doesnt go from Agar to Grain spawn bags <br /></blockquote><br /><br />Because grain spawn bags contain 5 to 7 quarts of grains. I like to inoculate a quart jar as a master first, and then use those to inoculate the larger spawn bags.&nbsp; This speeds up the process slightly, but the main reason is the agar to grain transfer is a potential vector of contamination, so it helps to keep your losses to a minimum.<br /><br />It's certainly possible to go from agar to spawn bag, just risky.<br />RR","title":"Re: Why does RR go Agar>Master>Jar>Bag","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}